data.message: Did you guys really drop God's Mom's life insurance policy because they missed two payments?  You kept all the rest of the money too, I assume?  I can only guess that when people are dying that some bills might go late, ya know?

You're scum. This company refuses to pay out money that is owed for stupid reasons. They're crooked and shady. Don't do business with these people. Bring your business elsewhere, lest you find yourself in a position where your loved one dies and you get left with nothing... Because that's what will happen if you use these people. 

Pay out what's owed, you crooks! And it's funny, because this backlash looks like it might get media attention pretty soon since so many people are outraged by it. I'd say that'll take much, much more out of your pockets than $300k, but to each their own, I suppose. 

Good luck with that.
Oh man. You guys fucked with God? You are about to witness the power of social media. Sucks to be you. Probably shouldn't have screwed over an innocent man.
Coming home to roost? ;-) Karma's a bitch!
Grab the torches and let us start a BOYCOTT NEW YORK LIFE INSURANCE PAGE!!!!!!MUHAHAHAHAHAHA! PAY GOD!!!!
You are scumbags! You continued to accept payments on a policy you knew an elderly couple would not be able to claim when the wife died because they missed 2 payments, HUM sounds like fraud to me!
what a bunch of lowlifes ... the word is out. we will do everything in our power to tell EVERYONE about your brand. enjoy hell
I knew insurance companies were mercenary, but refusing to pay life insurance over two missed payments?  May karma come back and bite you in the ass.
You've probably figured out by now that giving God's dad his pay out would be the best PR you've done all year.  God has a lot of followers.

You guys are a cruel and nasty joke. Being one of the many voices here to say your company denied the 'insurance' for a family who needed it most when they lost a dearly loved one and had nowhere to turn for help. Mind you they didn't ask for us to insult or defame you, we just can't stand to have a greedy company suck up all their wealth and give nothing back when the only fault they had was missing a payment or two.
Happy holidays, you curs.
You suck!!!!!!!!
Seriously...maybe people should be more important than profits... Maybe you can prove that insurance companies can be any better than scam artists?
After hearing that you refused to pay out on a policy after two missed payments during these hard economic times, I will reward your lack of understanding with a lack of my business.
You guys messed up. I bet you didn't realize that you would be loosing every amount of support you have. I hope you go bankrupt. You need to pay these poor people. soulless bastards.
Insurance, the biggest dirtbag scam I've ever heard of...

There's nothing here that hasn't been said already, some statements by people more eloquent than I can ever hope to be. 

And I agree with every one of them. 

Choke on your turkey, you jerks.

Time for a quick turn-around before this blows up in your face... Oh wait, it just did! 
Heartless!

just heard what shits you guys were to the guy who just lost his wife because he missed two payments.  you insurance scammers are what's wrong with this country.  i can't wait for your karma to fall on you.

You swindlers ought to be ashamed of yourselves, if you're even capable of feeling shame.  A good man lost his wife, close to the holidays no less, and you refuse to pay out his life insurance.  Why?  Because he missed two payments a long time ago.  Instead of sending him a message telling him that nullifies his policy and allowing him a chance to start over with another company, you continued to take his money - money you already knew you were never going to pay to him.  You swindled him and destroyed his life.  You people are horrible.  I'll never do business with you and tell everyone I know to avoid you like the plague.
For a company to accept payments on a policy they know to be null and void is fraud. "Keeping good going" must only be for stockholders, not policyholders.
People like you always get what their comeuppance. I feel sorry for the people who do business with you while your lack of professional integrity remains unbeknownst to them.
Shame on you!!!!!!!!!!

My husband and I will be removing our policy Friday morning.  You shouldn't treat people poorly.  A man just lost his wife, and all you can do is dig for the loopholes so you don't have to pay out the policy?? Such shame.  Merry Christmas...jerks.  God and his family do not deserve this kind of treatment in their grief.

Bet you didn't see this coming 
; )
Terrible people at new york life insurance.

You continue to bill an old couple, then claim the wives policy is "null" after she dies, over only two payments?  Did you even notify the poor couple of the missed payments, or did you just chuckle like cartoon villains because you knew you could use it as a loophole to not pay out when time came for it?  You're abominable.  I can't wait until the US wises up and gets rid of all you predatory insurance companies and goes Single Payer.  How do you people even sleep at night?  May you choke on your ill gained profits.

I seriously doubt that anyone at an insurance company who has the authority to make decisions about policy payouts is capable of feeling shame, but SHAME ON YOU anyway, for stiffing God's dad on his wife's policy. God knows, as do all his followers, that you've made enough profit from all the premiums you've collected to date. I hope He pushes the 'SMITE' button on your company. Glad I don't do business with you.
You should pay out the money to God's dad. Two missed payments is not enough to justify not paying him. For shame.

You are really giving the insurance industry a bad reputation. I am disgusted at your unethical business practices, taking advantage of God's family and increasing their suffering during a difficult time. Are you proud???
Sure would be nice if you weren't such assholes.  I know who I'll be avoiding for my future insurance needs, you worthless, greedy bastards.

Denying to pay out an insurance policy because of missed payments when you continued to bill for and receive payments after said missed payments is despicable.  You fooled God's dad into thinking that his policy was still active and would be honored by continuing to accept payments after the missed payments.  The right thing to do would be to pay up!
Shame on you.
Two missed payments, and God's Dad is screwed. You should be ashamed of yourselves.

Seriously?  Somebody pays for one of your crappy policies for YEARS and you deny their claim because of TWO MISSED PAYMENTS?

You people are the devil.  No, really.  You are the devil.  How do you live with yourselves?

So am I to believe that someone defaults on 2 payments of life insurance that means you do not inform them of the default and use it as a scape goat to paying out their policy. For shame. You should all be held accountable for your unscrupulous actions.
How do you not pay out on a policy because a customer missed two payments?? really? Get a heart...

God's mom missed two payments and now you refuse her life insurance policy? You really think that's a wise move? I mean seriously all this time you've used "acts of God" to get out of paying countless other claims and you can't make an exception??
You are horrible people.

I have just learnt that you have refused to pay out on the life insurance of God's mother who missed 2 premium payments on her policy before she passed away!  This leaves her already distraught and grieving family also worrying about how they will continue to pay the mortgage repayments and her retired husband now has no income.  You should be ashamed of yourselves.  it is true, Insurance Companies are in league with the devil!
